WEBVTT

00:01.230 --> 00:02.925
[narrator]
Previously on "Being Human."

00:02.969 --> 00:05.291
I got my residency at SCH.

00:05.330 --> 00:07.059
The hospital?
The one that I work at?

00:07.100 --> 00:09.159
What I really wanted
was to see you.

00:09.210 --> 00:11.406
Hear from you why you left.

00:11.440 --> 00:13.579
The night Stu died,

00:13.610 --> 00:16.500
when I was mauled,
the attack changed me.

00:16.550 --> 00:17.847
[groaning]

00:17.880 --> 00:18.904
Reaper...

00:18.950 --> 00:20.509
You could take my job.

00:20.550 --> 00:23.417
Be a reaper.
[screaming]

00:23.450 --> 00:25.714
You'll reap your
first soul tomorrow.

00:25.750 --> 00:27.013
Maybe I can do this.

00:27.060 --> 00:28.380
Suren knows about me?
That I'm back?

00:28.420 --> 00:31.026
- You really want him at your side?
- Yes.

00:31.060 --> 00:33.392
If you wanna buy your way
back into this court,

00:33.430 --> 00:35.751
Mother's going to want
her pound of flesh.

00:35.800 --> 00:37.723
Of course, a vampire
wouldn't die from this.

00:37.770 --> 00:38.965
Your skin will grow back.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.094
Henry is my blood,

00:41.140 --> 00:44.201
and he had better be alive
when I come back for him.

00:44.240 --> 00:47.232
<i>*Xk</i>

00:50.210 --> 00:52.349
[doorbell buzzing]

00:55.450 --> 00:56.542
Who is it?

00:56.590 --> 00:58.046
I don't know.

00:58.090 --> 00:59.387
You didn't check?
You always check.

00:59.420 --> 01:00.683
Old Sally checked.

01:00.720 --> 01:01.949
[doorbell continues buzzing]

01:06.260 --> 01:09.195
I need you to invite us in.

01:09.230 --> 01:10.959
You mean, you need me
to invite him in.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.138
I thought we didn't do that.

01:12.170 --> 01:14.696
This is different,
this is Henry. Uh...

01:14.740 --> 01:17.300
It was a long time ago, but...

01:17.340 --> 01:19.138
[whispering] I made him, Josh.

01:19.180 --> 01:22.206
He's... my son.

01:22.250 --> 01:23.877
Did you make him without skin?!

01:23.910 --> 01:25.071
I need a place
where I know he'll be safe.

01:25.110 --> 01:26.646
That's here.
Please.

01:26.680 --> 01:28.079
[Josh narrating] The bonds
you form with some people

01:28.120 --> 01:30.316
will make you
look past anything,

01:30.350 --> 01:31.909
ignore what they've become.

01:31.950 --> 01:34.112
Fine.

01:34.160 --> 01:36.083
Please, little bit more, huh?

01:36.130 --> 01:37.450
Enter.
I invite thee.

01:37.490 --> 01:40.096
- Mi casa, su casa.
- That'll do.

01:40.130 --> 01:42.599
[Josh narrating] You'll hang onto
the version you wanna remember,

01:42.630 --> 01:45.395
- _not the one
in front of you now.

01:45.430 --> 01:48.297
I can't deal with this.
I'm late for work.

01:48.340 --> 01:49.307
[door closes]

01:49.340 --> 01:51.763
Me, too.

01:51.810 --> 01:54.780
<i>*Xk</i>

01:54.810 --> 01:57.802
[children playing, laughing]

01:59.920 --> 02:01.410
I don't wanna sound
like an infomercial,

02:01.450 --> 02:04.579
but attitude is everything.

02:04.620 --> 02:07.385
To do this right, you need
to lose the ambivalence.

02:07.420 --> 02:11.186
Y-Y-You act like it's easy
to kill your own kind.

02:11.230 --> 02:13.619
To stand there and watch
while you shred isn't easy.

02:13.660 --> 02:16.368
I never said it was easy.
I said it was necessary.

02:16.400 --> 02:17.697
Either way,

02:17.730 --> 02:19.698
a ghost is gone.

02:19.740 --> 02:20.866
Somebody just like me.

02:20.900 --> 02:23.835
This has to be done,
but it doesn't have to be cruel.

02:23.870 --> 02:26.771
After all, we're reapers,
not monsters.

02:26.810 --> 02:29.199
S-Somebody Kills a body,

02:29.250 --> 02:32.049
and their soul is still left.

02:32.080 --> 02:33.673
But, when you do what we do...

02:33.720 --> 02:36.018
He needs to go.

02:38.250 --> 02:39.888
I know.

02:39.920 --> 02:43.356
[ominous music plays *]

02:43.390 --> 02:46.325
Walter.

02:46.360 --> 02:49.295
Walter.

02:49.870 --> 02:52.089
Go find your own kid.

02:52.130 --> 02:54.394
He's mine.

02:54.440 --> 02:55.464
Hey!

02:55.500 --> 02:58.367
What the...?

02:58.410 --> 02:59.935
You said you were
done possessing.

02:59.980 --> 03:02.745
So?
I slipped once.

03:02.780 --> 03:04.248
I'm sorry, Walter.

03:04.280 --> 03:06.669
Reapers don't apologize.
Come on, Sally!

03:06.720 --> 03:07.915
Think how that reflects on me.

03:07.950 --> 03:09.679
What are you talking about?

03:09.720 --> 03:12.519
Walter, it's time for you to go.

03:12.560 --> 03:14.915
Ooh, a catchphrase!
I like it.

03:14.960 --> 03:17.588
Get out of my face.
I-I can control it.

03:17.630 --> 03:20.600
Not today, you didn't. Not
yesterday, with that waitress.

03:20.630 --> 03:22.394
Or last week,
with the bus driver.

03:22.430 --> 03:24.922
- You're never gonna stop.
- [Reaper] Do it.

03:24.970 --> 03:27.894
- [groaning] Sally, stop!
- [Reaper] That's it.

03:27.940 --> 03:30.966
Shred him!
Oh, come on.

03:31.010 --> 03:33.069
What did I teach you?

03:33.110 --> 03:34.236
Strike.
- [Walter] No, please!

03:34.280 --> 03:36.374
[grunting]

03:36.410 --> 03:39.380
[Sally panting]

03:39.420 --> 03:42.879
[sighs]
Not my best work, but...

03:42.920 --> 03:44.479
You get the point.

03:44.520 --> 03:48.388
[Josh narrating]
Friends, parents, mentors.

03:48.420 --> 03:51.128
We hold on to that
idealized image of them,

03:51.160 --> 03:53.049
even if it's an illusion.

03:53.100 --> 03:55.899
Because if we can't
believe in them,

03:55.930 --> 03:58.524
what does that say about us?

03:58.570 --> 04:01.540
<i>*Xk</i>

04:01.570 --> 04:04.540
[faint chatter]

04:08.280 --> 04:10.647
Excuse me.

04:10.680 --> 04:12.409
Hey, what's this,
what's this all about?

04:12.450 --> 04:15.374
- Sexual harassment seminar's today.
- It's mandatory.

04:15.420 --> 04:17.445
Shoot me in the face.

04:17.490 --> 04:18.548
Hey.

04:19.820 --> 04:21.788
Hey.
[clears throat]

04:24.130 --> 04:27.589
Uh, that coffee's toxic.

04:27.630 --> 04:30.827
- Thanks for the heads up.
- Yeah.

04:30.870 --> 04:32.964
Josh, wait.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.365
[chuckles]

04:34.400 --> 04:36.960
We can't be these people.

04:37.010 --> 04:38.466
Which people?

04:38.510 --> 04:41.138
The coworker exes
who talk about cafeteria food

04:41.180 --> 04:43.899
and give "What up?”
nods in the hall.

04:43.950 --> 04:46.817
- Yeah, those people suck.
- Yeah.

04:46.850 --> 04:49.069
So, I've been thinking,

04:49.120 --> 04:51.441
you were a lousy fianc, but

04:51.490 --> 04:53.857
you were a pretty decent friend.

04:53.890 --> 04:55.517
Thank you?

04:55.560 --> 04:58.985
- Josh, we were friends a lot longer than we were engaged.
- Yeah, I know, yeah.

04:59.030 --> 05:00.828
Friends we can do.

05:00.860 --> 05:04.364
Oh, and, uh, all that rage
you say you got,

05:04.400 --> 05:06.596
I don't see it.

05:06.640 --> 05:09.803
Your bark was always worse
than your bite.

05:09.840 --> 05:12.502
[Josh narrating] Remembering
that best version of our friends

05:12.540 --> 05:15.134
reminds us that we were
that promising once.

05:15.180 --> 05:17.979
That strong, that alive.

05:18.010 --> 05:20.877
[suspenseful music plays *]

05:24.450 --> 05:26.214
Stu?

05:26.250 --> 05:28.753
Hey, Levs...
[weakly chuckles]

05:28.790 --> 05:30.224
Stu...

05:32.600 --> 05:36.195
I can't believe you're here!

05:36.230 --> 05:37.391
How've you been since...

05:37.430 --> 05:40.730
Since you convinced me to go
camping with you that night?

05:40.770 --> 05:42.704
[overlapping chatter]

05:44.070 --> 05:46.402
I've been dead, Josh.

05:46.440 --> 05:48.329
How 'bout you?

05:50.810 --> 05:53.848
<i>*Xk</i>

06:00.920 --> 06:02.479
Man, you have no idea

06:02.530 --> 06:03.656
how many times

06:03.690 --> 06:05.727
I wish I had you
around to talk to.

06:05.760 --> 06:07.057
Yeah?

06:07.100 --> 06:09.569
You could've tried to find me.

06:09.600 --> 06:12.262
Um... To be honest,

06:12.300 --> 06:15.497
once I found out
that ghosts are real, I...

06:15.540 --> 06:17.736
didn't really wanna see you.

06:17.770 --> 06:19.772
You really know how to make
a guy feel missed.

06:19.810 --> 06:21.505
No, that's not what I'm-I'm...

06:21.540 --> 06:23.599
I just meant that...

06:23.650 --> 06:25.573
I... hoped that you'd
gotten your door

06:25.610 --> 06:27.044
and moved on to something

06:27.080 --> 06:28.218
better than...
- Josh...

06:28.250 --> 06:30.981
[scoffs] My dad never said,
"I love you," and

06:31.020 --> 06:33.455
my mother basically
cut my food for me

06:33.490 --> 06:35.618
until I went off to college, so,

06:35.660 --> 06:39.290
I am the king
of unresolved issues, life

06:39.330 --> 06:40.991
and afterlife.

06:41.030 --> 06:43.260
No door for me.

06:43.300 --> 06:46.099
So, what did you do?

06:46.130 --> 06:48.736
I stayed pissed at you

06:48.770 --> 06:52.035
for far too long for, uh,

06:52.070 --> 06:55.131
surviving, leaving.

06:55.180 --> 06:58.480
I don't know how you
got over it, but I'm...

06:58.510 --> 07:01.912
glad you did.

07:01.950 --> 07:03.645
[sentimental music plays *]

07:03.690 --> 07:05.146
Grab was flawless.

07:05.190 --> 07:08.717
Kid barely knew
he'd been possessed.

07:08.760 --> 07:10.956
You've gotta make sure
the shred is just as clean.

07:10.990 --> 07:12.799
You make it sound so clinical.

07:12.830 --> 07:14.594
It should be.

07:14.630 --> 07:17.691
If you linger, they start in
with the whining and the lying.

07:19.700 --> 07:22.863
It gets awkward for everyone.

07:26.580 --> 07:28.503
You're still not sold.

07:30.580 --> 07:31.979
It's just...

07:33.650 --> 07:36.779
When Walter said that
it was a one time thing,

07:36.820 --> 07:41.155
or when Stevie told me that he
didn't kill Boner and his friends.

07:41.190 --> 07:42.828
How do we know
who's telling the truth?

07:42.860 --> 07:44.282
They all lie.

07:45.990 --> 07:47.799
Wouldn't you, to save yourself?

07:47.830 --> 07:49.559
Maybe.

07:50.600 --> 07:52.466
What if we make a mistake?

07:52.500 --> 07:54.195
There are no mistakes.

07:54.240 --> 07:56.265
Once you take over,
that'll become clear.

07:56.300 --> 07:58.439
- How?
- Commit,

07:58.470 --> 08:00.939
and the worries will go away.

08:00.980 --> 08:03.699
Will that be a problem?

08:06.010 --> 08:06.841
No.

08:06.880 --> 08:08.848
Good.

08:08.880 --> 08:11.850
"Cause the next reap
is all yours.

08:17.930 --> 08:20.228
How did you even find me here?

08:20.260 --> 08:22.866
Uh, remember DUI Dave,

08:22.900 --> 08:24.629
always riding a stool
down Durgen's?

08:24.670 --> 08:26.832
Yes!
Took out 40 feet of guardrail

08:26.870 --> 08:28.395
when he drove into the gorge.

08:28.440 --> 08:29.498
- Yeah.
- I remember that guy.

08:29.540 --> 08:32.464
Yeah, that's the one.
Well, homeboy's like a

08:32.510 --> 08:34.568
clearing house
for the supernatural now.

08:34.610 --> 08:37.341
So, I heard through
the ghost-vine that you're a

08:37.380 --> 08:38.847
werewolf?

08:38.880 --> 08:40.518
You're kind of a big deal
back home.

08:40.549 --> 08:42.211
Great.
I'm huge in Ithaca.

08:42.250 --> 08:44.241
- Right?
- Yeah.

08:45.690 --> 08:48.853
You know, sometimes I-I wish
I hadn't left so fast,

08:48.890 --> 08:51.587
but the whole wolf thing
kinda spun me out a little bit.

08:51.630 --> 08:54.656
Yeah, that-that night
messed up a lot of us.

08:54.700 --> 08:57.897
- Your parents got even weirder.
- Tell me about it.

08:57.930 --> 08:59.739
Julia...

08:59.770 --> 09:03.001
Yeah, but she's doing better.

09:03.040 --> 09:06.670
I mean, sh-she even wants
to be my friend.

09:06.710 --> 09:08.439
Yeah, I-I

09:08.480 --> 09:11.199
would pass on that.

09:11.250 --> 09:12.445
Why?

09:12.480 --> 09:15.040
Well...

09:15.080 --> 09:18.084
You guys are both “all in" kind of people.
- I was.

09:18.120 --> 09:20.851
I was.
I am not anymore.

09:20.890 --> 09:21.812
[chuckling] Yeah.

09:21.860 --> 09:24.056
No, for real, I'm-I'm...

09:24.090 --> 09:26.354
I went all in with my last
girlfriend, Nora,

09:26.390 --> 09:29.496
and, and now... She's gone.

09:29.530 --> 09:32.420
She's gone away or

09:32.470 --> 09:33.289
she's gone, dead?

09:33.340 --> 09:36.435
No, she's alive.

09:36.470 --> 09:38.768
And she's a wolf.

09:38.810 --> 09:40.209
[inhaling]

09:40.240 --> 09:42.675
Yeah.

09:42.710 --> 09:45.771
She wants nothing to do with me.

09:46.950 --> 09:49.578
So, I guess Julia
actually got off easy?

09:49.620 --> 09:52.180
Yes, she did.

09:53.190 --> 09:56.455
And don't worry,
nothing is gonna change that.

09:56.490 --> 09:59.755
Julia and I are officially
ancient history.

09:59.800 --> 10:02.792
<i>*Xk</i>

10:03.830 --> 10:05.719
[groaning in pain]

10:05.770 --> 10:07.693
I know you have one around here.

10:07.740 --> 10:09.094
One?
One what?

10:09.140 --> 10:09.959
A stake.

10:10.010 --> 10:12.001
No, no.
You're gonna...

10:12.040 --> 10:13.178
get better.
You're strong.

10:13.210 --> 10:14.735
No, I'm not.

10:14.780 --> 10:17.147
- I never was.
- Hey...

10:17.180 --> 10:19.740
you made it 80 years
in the wilderness.

10:19.780 --> 10:22.886
- You can make it through this.
- Why?

10:22.920 --> 10:26.015
So I can screw up again?

10:26.050 --> 10:29.054
Make your life worse
like I always have?

10:30.690 --> 10:32.920
Not always.

10:34.530 --> 10:37.522
[overlapping shouting, gunfire]

10:43.670 --> 10:45.160
What do we got here?

10:45.210 --> 10:47.531
Cleared a whole trench
by himself.

10:47.580 --> 10:49.207
I've never seen so much blood.

10:49.240 --> 10:51.971
How many entry wounds are there?

10:52.010 --> 10:54.980
Lost count at a dozen.

10:55.020 --> 10:57.079
You deal with him.

10:58.420 --> 11:00.684
I'm afraid you're stuck with me.

11:03.190 --> 11:06.023
Let's see what we have here.

11:08.830 --> 11:11.094
[gasp]
Dear Lord...

11:13.700 --> 11:15.134
They'll be gone west by morning.

11:15.170 --> 11:16.899
Don't go wasting
good morphine on a dead man.

11:20.540 --> 11:21.871
[grunting]

11:22.950 --> 11:24.679
Take them out.

11:24.710 --> 11:25.905
What?

11:25.950 --> 11:28.044
The bullets.
You heard him.

11:28.080 --> 11:30.549
I'm dead anyway.
Get them out!

11:35.590 --> 11:38.628
[labored breathing]

11:48.700 --> 11:51.704
[groaning]

12:02.420 --> 12:03.512
Wait here.

12:11.530 --> 12:14.693
Uh-uh, I'm not babysitting
the meatsicle.

12:14.730 --> 12:15.959
It's not like he's gonna
throw a rager.

12:16.000 --> 12:18.560
He's not getting any better,
and he needs food.

12:18.600 --> 12:20.466
Oh, are we talking takeout
that comes in a bag,

12:20.500 --> 12:22.559
or the kind with a pulse?

12:22.600 --> 12:24.068
You know what?
Never mind.

12:24.110 --> 12:27.102
Bring him a whole herd
of cattle. What do I care?

12:30.480 --> 12:31.606
[door slams]

12:31.650 --> 12:35.518
Hey, Sally.

12:35.550 --> 12:37.746
- Boner?
- You seen Stevie?

12:37.790 --> 12:38.916
[Sally]
We know about Boner.

12:38.950 --> 12:42.284
- Boner, he's still here!
- Where, where is he?

12:42.320 --> 12:44.379
But Stevie shredded you.

12:44.430 --> 12:46.159
That's news to me.
Who told you that?

12:46.190 --> 12:48.158
[Reaper]
He shredded them, Sally.

12:48.200 --> 12:49.656
Dylan, Boner.

12:49.700 --> 12:51.464
Stevie lied to you.

12:52.940 --> 12:54.738
Someone who should know better.

12:56.170 --> 12:57.831
Are you okay?

12:57.870 --> 12:59.508
Yeah.

12:59.540 --> 13:00.769
"Cause you don't look okay.

13:00.810 --> 13:03.347
No, I'm fine, um...

13:04.650 --> 13:08.541
So-So, the other guys
at Jasper's...

13:08.580 --> 13:10.344
Stevie didn't shred any of them?

13:10.390 --> 13:11.949
The only one Stevie shredded
was Dylan,

13:11.990 --> 13:13.856
and that was to protect you.

13:13.890 --> 13:16.882
Who told you that stuff
about Stevie?

13:19.130 --> 13:22.862
A ghost reaper.
That's who told me.

13:22.900 --> 13:25.164
You never saw him at Jasper's?

13:25.200 --> 13:26.599
No.

13:26.630 --> 13:28.189
Is he after Stevie?

13:28.240 --> 13:30.504
<i>*Xk</i>

13:32.510 --> 13:34.672
Not anymore.

13:35.810 --> 13:37.608
Good.

13:37.650 --> 13:40.119
If you see Stevie, tell him
to come hang out with us again.

13:40.150 --> 13:42.369
Nobody's seen him lately.

13:43.820 --> 13:45.117
[panting]

13:46.190 --> 13:50.058
Offensive conduct doesn't
even have to be sexual.

13:50.090 --> 13:51.182
Language,

13:51.230 --> 13:54.359
singling out somebody
based on gender.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.797
Even staring,

13:58.830 --> 14:02.061
if it's combined
with threatening behavior.

14:02.100 --> 14:04.330
N-Now, that all being said,

14:04.370 --> 14:09.001
we know that coworkers
are gonna have sexual relations.

14:09.040 --> 14:11.646
I'm sure that some of you
already have.

14:11.680 --> 14:14.012
But, most harassment
cases happen

14:14.050 --> 14:16.473
when there's an unequal
power dynamic.

14:16.520 --> 14:19.683
Like between, say, a doctor
and an orderly.

14:19.720 --> 14:21.381
...to make sure that it's put
to a stop

14:21.420 --> 14:23.559
before things get
out of control.

14:23.590 --> 14:25.058
Man speaks the truth.

14:25.090 --> 14:26.387
I get it.

14:30.270 --> 14:32.932
[whispering]
Everyone is looking at you.

14:32.970 --> 14:34.369
It's the story of my life.

14:34.400 --> 14:37.563
Try getting left at the altar.

14:37.610 --> 14:39.567
[speaker] I have a little rule when
it comes to sexual harassment,

14:39.610 --> 14:40.702
especially if you've
been warned.

14:40.740 --> 14:44.404
And that is, when in doubt,
cut it out.

14:44.450 --> 14:45.906
[light laughter]

14:45.950 --> 14:47.873
If you have any questions,

14:47.920 --> 14:51.686
you can always come to me, to my
office for a private one-on-one.

14:51.720 --> 14:54.712
- That's not at all creepy.
- [laughing]

14:56.020 --> 14:59.957
I guess we'll just, uh, wait
'til our coworkers are finished.

15:00.000 --> 15:02.298
- [clearing throat]
- Oh, good, they've finished.

15:02.330 --> 15:04.594
[chuckles]
Now, what exactly

15:04.630 --> 15:07.497
is harassment?

15:07.540 --> 15:10.464
<i>*Xk</i>

15:10.510 --> 15:13.502
[overlapping chatter, giggling]

15:15.310 --> 15:16.971
...And that's, that's
not what I'm saying.

15:17.010 --> 15:18.808
What you were thinking about what I'm saying...
- [laughing]

15:18.850 --> 15:20.978
The dog could not be, uh,

15:21.020 --> 15:24.513
persuaded to go.

15:24.550 --> 15:26.712
[dog barking]

15:26.750 --> 15:27.717
